For every Result r and every Presenter method X, stripANSI(ColorPresenter.X(r)) MUST equal PlainPresenter.X(r) byte-for-byte. This is the correctness invariant that makes Color safe to implement independently of Plain. It is enforced by spot-check tests covering synced, drifted marker, drifted spec, multi-event closures, empty state, and unlinked warning shapes. See <ref spec="output_impl.guardrail_test">guardrail test</ref>.